and they're cutting
to a car chase?

1819
01:18:49,458 --> 01:18:51,193
I would like to watch
the car chase.

1820
01:18:51,194 --> 01:18:52,828
You need to shut your mouth.

1821
01:18:52,828 --> 01:18:52,828
RON: <i>This is</i>
<i>extremely gripping.</i>

1822
01:18:52,828 --> 01:18:56,864
<i>Oh! Oh! He just hit a car!</i>
<i>He just hit a car!</i>

1823
01:18:56,865 --> 01:18:58,033
He hit a car!
Did you see that?

1824
01:18:58,033 --> 01:19:00,234
He hit a car!
RON: <i>Wow!</i>

1825
01:19:00,235 --> 01:19:01,903
He hit the car!
He hit the car!

1826
01:19:01,904 --> 01:19:04,872
When did the news get awesome?
(ALL WHOOPING)

1827
01:19:04,873 --> 01:19:06,774
RON: <i>And he just</i>
<i>loses it! Wow!</i>

1828
01:19:06,775 --> 01:19:08,476
That's exactly what we needed.

1829
01:19:08,478 --> 01:19:10,659
It was getting a little boring...

1830
01:19:13,081 --> 01:19:15,382
Hey. You did
a great job.

1831
01:19:15,384 --> 01:19:17,786
Thanks, Gary.

1832
01:19:17,787 --> 01:19:19,320
I don't think your dad's coming.

1833
01:19:19,322 --> 01:19:21,141
I'm sorry, honey,
but I think we need to go.

1834
01:19:22,490 --> 01:19:24,524
Stop reading my mind!

1835
01:19:25,226 --> 01:19:26,426
All right.

1836
01:19:27,395 --> 01:19:28,996
(SIGHS)

1837
01:19:30,966 --> 01:19:32,565
I mean, this is
what I worry about.

1838
01:19:34,802 --> 01:19:36,771
WALTER: Did you do that
with your mind?

1839
01:19:36,773 --> 01:19:37,838
GARY: No.

1840
