1872
01:21:44,666 --> 01:21:47,135
NARRATOR:
<i>In the myth of Icarus,</i>

1873
01:21:47,136 --> 01:21:49,904
<i>Icarus, full of the folly</i>
<i>that comes with pride,</i>

1874
01:21:49,905 --> 01:21:51,238
<i>flew too high</i>

1875
01:21:51,239 --> 01:21:53,073
<i>and the sun melted his wings.</i>

1876
01:21:54,576 --> 01:21:58,313
<i>Burgundy's fame was bigger</i>
<i>than he ever imagined.</i>

1877
01:21:58,314 --> 01:22:01,015
<i>And the fall was dizzying.</i>

1878
01:22:02,449 --> 01:22:03,417
(ALL GASPING)

1879
01:22:05,552 --> 01:22:07,054
(SCREAMS)

1880
01:22:09,189 --> 01:22:10,524
LINDA: Oh, my God, Ronny!

1881
01:22:10,958 --> 01:22:12,993
Ron!

1882
01:22:12,994 --> 01:22:14,561
Open the bloody gate.
WOMAN: Will somebody call an ambulance?

1883
01:22:14,563 --> 01:22:16,563
Do not die in front of us!
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

1884
01:22:17,564 --> 01:22:20,167
Do not die in front of us!

1885
01:22:22,337 --> 01:22:24,171
Stay classy, Ron Burgundy.

1886
01:22:24,172 --> 01:22:25,572
MAN: Somebody
call an ambulance!

1887
01:22:37,452 --> 01:22:39,220
Damn it, Milton, what is it?

1888
01:22:39,220 --> 01:22:40,521
BRANGLEY: Well, Ron...

1889
01:22:40,523 --> 01:22:42,524
I, um...

1890
01:22:42,524 --> 01:22:45,493
It looks as if both optic nerves

1891
01:22:45,493 --> 01:22:48,662
